@{
    ViewBag.Title = "GREWARE";
    ViewBag.Message = "ASP Net Pages Requirements";
}

<div class="container">
        <h2>Welcome to Agenda GREWARE</h2>
        <p>
            GREWARE Agenda is a sample application that demonstrates how to use Entity Framework in an ASP.NET MVC 5 web application.
        </p>
    <h2>Coding</h2>
    <p>Create and ASP NET Web Application with Visual Studio 2012 or 2012, and SQL Server 2008, 2012, 2014 Express Editions.</p>
        <h3>@ViewBag.Message</h3>
        <div class="list-group">
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">Create a web application with 3 layers coding, with Form Pages.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Create the pages needed to Add, Modify and Delete the information provided.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">The Page to add the information, should be able to add as many contact information and addresses as the customer want.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Use Entity Framework to manipulate the data</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Use CSS3 styles to create a fancy UI for the application.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">You can use jQuery and other UI frameworks to enhance the UI.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">You can use AJAX.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Create a Search Page to find the information</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h3>Extras (optional)</h3>
        <div class="list-group">
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">Instead of ASP NET Web Form application, create a MVC 5 Razor Engine Web Application.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Use AJAX and Modal Dialogs to do the Operations for Modify and Delete information..</li>
                <li class="list-group-item">Create a Web Service to Serve the Methods to Add, Modify and Delete..</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    <h3>Database Requirements</h3>
    <div class="list-group">
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">Create a script to create a new database called “Agenda”, with all the information needed and the tables mentioned forward.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Add 3 tables to the database: Persons, Contact Info, and Addresses.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Normalize the tables and do the relations.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Add all the fields as you want, to do a strong database, take in mind that 1 person can have a lot of contact information details (in example: 3 phones and 4 mails), also the same person can live in different places, so the addresses will be many as well.</li>
         </ul>
</div>


